Even though I altered this recipe a little to suit my taste, I am giving it 4 stars b/c it is a great core recipe for a fabulous dip. It is the best version of Artichoke dip I have tasted thus far. The substitutions I made were as follows: added a big clove of minced fresh garlic, deleted the marjoram and the onion salt but added a touch of kosher salt to make up for it, used freshly grated parmaggiano reggiano instead of the romano, and used full fat mayo and sour cream (I know, I'm naughty, but it was for company, after all.) I served it with bagel chips and my guests went crazy for it. I love the fact that this version uses substanitally less mayo and/or sour cream than traditional recipes. Not only is it healthier, but it allowed the taste of the artichokes to be more in the forefront. This recipe does not yield a lot, however, so if you are making it for a large crowd you may want to consider doubling it. Fabulous recipe, thank you!

