I made this for a party and it was just "okay" -- the restaurant's version must be superior to the home version because it simply wasn't that tasty. I made the following Hot Spinach and Artichoke Dip for Superbowl and it was delicious: Using an electric mixer, mix 6 ounces cream cheese, 1/2 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 1/2 cup grated parmesan cheese, 1 or 2 minced garlic cloves, 1t red pepper flakes, 1T Worcestershire sauce and a healthy squeeze of fresh lemon juice. Fold in by hand 1 cup thawed chopped spinach (squeezed dry) and two 13-1/2 oz cans of artichoke hearts roughly chopped. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Put in a baking dish and bake at 400-degrees for about 30 minutes until bubbling and brown on top.

