You can simplify this dip to make a fabulous topping for bruschetta. Mix real mayo, chopped artichoke hearts (marinated or not), parmesan and scallions (optional). Spread on baguette slices and broil until they bubble. Quick and delicious!

Rating: 0
I have been making a baked artichoke dip for years with rave reviews. Its very easy! 2 cups Hellman's regular mayo, 2 cups (or more) shredded asiago cheese, minced garlic (2 or 3 cloves), 14 oz. marinated artichoke hearts chopped. Mix together (can be done day before). Hollow out round loaf of bread (save innards). Put dip in hollowed out loaf and bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees. Serve with chopped bread (from the middle of the loaf and another loaf too). Its wonderful and oh so easy. Everyone will ask you for the recipe.

